1
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:42,360
Weiwei,

2
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:44,170
you're back.

3
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:47,340
Look, you got this question wrong again.

4
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:58,840
Mom.

5
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,160
Weiwei,

6
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,240
don't be sad.

7
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:10,639
Mom,

8
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,200
you don't know

9
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,600
how hard I worked before.

10
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,920
I just wanted to fulfill your dream.

11
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,400
Didn't you always say

12
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,960
you wanted to see the moon?

13
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,079
You took my words

14
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,960
to heart.

15
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,530
They took root and sprouted in your heart,

16
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:38,300
so didn't they become your own dream?

17
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,520
Being able to pursue your own dream,

18
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,680
what a happy thing it is.

19
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,380
I don't want to pursue it anymore.

20
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,240
You're gone.

21
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,240
Mr. Qin, who has always guided me,

22
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,320
also fell ill.

23
00:02:57,079 --> 00:02:58,880
Don't be swayed by these things.

24
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,840
Your Mr. Qin,

25
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,260
I believe he has persevered all his life.

26
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,600
Even if he is sick now,

27
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,530
he must still be holding on.

28
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,080
Mom,

29
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:13,800
why didn't you

30
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,720
tell me earlier back then?

31
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,920
I didn't even get to see you one last time.

32
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,160
I miss you so much.

33
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,040
For so many years, I thought I had moved on.

34
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,000
I haven't.

35
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:32,840
Why did you all hide it from me?

36
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,079
Because Mom was scared too.

37
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,920
Mom was afraid you wouldn't understand these things.

38
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,040
How I wish all this was fake,

39
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,660
and everything could start over.

40
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:55,200
But I know everything is true.

41
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,840
I can't do anything.

42
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,580
Mom knows how much you are suffering,

43
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:07,800
and also believes

44
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,600
you can definitely overcome it.

45
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,680
Think of your Mr. Qin.

46
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:17,560
Compared to the happiness of pursuing a dream,

47
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,540
what does this little pain amount to?

48
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,560
Mom thanks you.

49
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,120
In the past,

50
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,000
I was also just like this,

51
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,600
shut outside this door.

52
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,540
When I was still young.

53
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:55,650
The year my mom got sick,

54
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,320
they kept it from me

55
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,540
and didn't tell me.

56
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,160
Until my mom passed away,

57
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,690
I never got to see her for the last time.

58
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,400
They were afraid,

59
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:29,280
afraid of me seeing her in pain.

60
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:36,720
They just wanted me to remember my mom's good side.

61
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,680
But did they ever ask for my opinion?

62
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,680
If I knew that

63
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,970
the older a person's memories are,

64
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,120
the clearer they become,

65
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,680
I might...

66
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,440
Ying Ziqi.

67
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,840
You are my brother.

68
00:07:45,159 --> 00:07:46,960
You are my best friend.

69
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,480
Why did even you hide it from me?

70
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:18,760
Qin.

71
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,560
Qin.

72
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:25,840
Qin.

73
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:33,900
The surgery was very successful.

74
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,200
Get a good rest.

75
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:42,600
Mr. Qin,

76
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,800
you need to get well soon.

77
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,920
We are all here

78
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:48,240
waiting for you to come back.

79
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,480
All right.

80
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,970
Everyone head back for now.

81
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:06,480
Let's go.

82
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:09,720
Let's go.

83
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:32,560
Okay.

84
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,840
I'll keep an eye on things here.

85
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,320
You guys go back and get to work.

86
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,000
Try to get

87
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,720
good news for Mr. Qin as soon as possible.

88
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,320
You should get some rest too.

89
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:44,000
We'll take turns looking after him for the next few days.

90
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:44,680
No need.

91
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,680
Just head back first, okay?

92
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,720
I'll let you know if I need anything.

93
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,320
Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.

94
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:53,400
Let's go.

95
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:54,920
Let's go.

96
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,930
I've adjusted the plan.

97
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,770
Let's start the test directly.

98
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,170
For this debugging,

99
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,840
we've eliminated faults in the telemetry and data transmission subsystem,

100
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:47,300
and added several fault contingency plans.

101
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,320
On my end,

102
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:50,680
it can basically be considered passed.

103
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,440
If the physical vehicle test

104
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,800
requires any additions,

105
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,930
we'll add them then.

106
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,640
Wu Wei, what do you think?

107
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:08,280
Let me emphasize this again.

108
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,120
We don't have much time left.

109
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,680
I hope

110
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:15,320
you can adjust your working state.

111
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:23,880
Wu Wei.

112
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,220
I'm talking to you.

113
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,480
I know you are upset.

114
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,500
But we are not doctors.

115
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,480
We can't cure Mr. Qin's illness.

116
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,800
As his student,

117
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,920
and an astronaut,

118
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:45,050
your primary goal is to complete the mission.

119
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,840
This is the best answer you can give him.

120
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,540
I think that's what Mr. Qin wants too.

121
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,290
Let's begin.

122
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:09,640
I'll operate.

123
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,170
You record the data.

124
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,120
Yes.

125
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,380
What happened?

126
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,600
Is there a fluctuation in the radar frequency?

127
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,240
Yes.

128
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,250
But I don't know the reason.

129
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:07,760
Let's redo it.

130
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,360
No.

131
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,040
I think we should take the radar with the abnormal frequency...

132
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:12,920
Adjust it,

133
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:13,920
and test it again.

134
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:14,680
Wu Wei.

135
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,580
No need to test.

136
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:20,160
The dust kicked up by the simulated lunar soil

137
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,690
affected Yutu's hardware.

138
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:23,360
Looking at this data,

139
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:26,440
such a small deviation won't affect the next test.

140
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:29,120
Yeah, maybe it's just an accident.

141
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,760
Since we've already started testing,

142
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:31,800
let's try again.

143
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,680
There are no accidents here.

144
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:36,720
If it fails, we start over from zero.

145
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,580
Aerospace is a race against time.

146
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:42,300
I don't want Yutu-2 to repeat the same mistakes.

147
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,080
No problem. No problem.

148
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,800
I can cooperate with you, no problem.

149
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,520
But we need a standard and a direction.

150
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,400
My standard

151
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:51,060
is that there can't be the slightest deviation.

152
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,640
Wu Wei, you saw it too.

153
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,760
The moon's gravity is weaker than Earth's.

154
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:57,800
Even dust stirred up during ground tests

155
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,160
can cause data fluctuations.

156
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:00,240
If we actually get to the moon

157
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,080
and something goes wrong,

158
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:03,080
everyone's efforts will be in vain.

159
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,040
The launch window is so tight.

160
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:07,000
We keep starting over

161
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:07,920
again and again.

162
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,720
Mr. Qin asks about our progress every day.

163
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:10,920
If we miss the window,

164
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:11,680
how can we explain it to him?

165
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:13,810
Are you doing this mission for Mr. Qin?

166
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,120
That's not what Wu Wei meant.

167
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,640
I don't care what you mean.

168
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:20,000
My point is very clear.

169
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,560
Start from zero.

170
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,200
Redo it.

171
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,720
If you are really doing this for Mr. Qin,

172
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,040
then finish all the tasks

173
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,040
I assigned to you.

174
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,800
Stop going against him.

175
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,560
The knot about Moon Rabbit I

176
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:40,800
has never been untied in his heart.

177
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,600
Nothing we say will be of any use.

178
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,120
If we follow his arrangement now

179
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,720
and start over from scratch,

180
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,200
I actually have a few papers for reference.

181
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,460
I have a new direction.

182
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,360
What are you doing?

183
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:09,120
Are you planning to land here?

184
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:11,050
This isn't the far side of the moon.

185
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:14,780
To take care of you.

186
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,160
Go back.

187
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,480
Did you hear me tell you to go back?

188
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,100
I'm not going back.

189
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:31,840
Where is Gu?

190
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:33,400
Call Gu for me.

191
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:35,760
It's no use calling anyone.

192
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,760
I'm not leaving.

193
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:42,360
What exactly do you want to do?

194
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,530
Such a big thing happened, and you kept it from me.

195
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:48,800
What about in the future?

196
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,530
Don't interfere with what I do.

197
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,210
What about the mission?

198
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,520
Don't worry about the mission.

199
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:58,680
I'll handle it.

200
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,840
From today until you are discharged from the hospital,

201
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:04,160
after I finish work every day,

202
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,819
I will come to take care of you.

203
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,250
If you find me annoying,

204
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,380
get better sooner.

205
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:14,000
No, I don't want to drink.

206
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,880
I've been waiting for you.

207
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:31,920
You didn't make a sound.

208
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:32,980
What are you doing?

209
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:35,900
Why are you messing with flowers?

210
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,300
Sister Nan.

211
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:43,050
Lao Qin loved this pot of flowers the most.

212
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:45,600
Now it's all withered.

213
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,480
He would be so sad if he knew.

214
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,320
Yeah.

215
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,360
Lao Qin took such good care of it.

216
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,520
Once a plant is left unattended,

217
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,480
it withers.

218
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,920
How could we forget?

219
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:08,240
It's okay.

220
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:11,320
We will water it every day

221
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:12,920
and take good care of it.

222
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,240
When it recovers,

223
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:16,060
Lao Qin will come back too.

224
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,140
Sister Nan.

225
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:23,000
I was a jerk before. I...

226
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:23,720
All right.

227
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,000
Let's drop it.

228
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,280
Let's work hard together,

229
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:32,410
and wait for Mr. Qin to come back, okay?

230
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:36,640
Let's go.

231
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:40,480
Mr. Qin is waiting.

232
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,450
Let's deliver the stuff first.

233
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:32,170
Where are you going?

234
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:36,880
I'm getting off work.

235
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:38,760
Is the data calculation done?

236
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:39,560
It's useless.

237
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,980
By your standards,

238
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:42,560
this proposal is still flawed.

239
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:44,420
You'll just shoot it down anyway.

240
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,400
Come, slowly.

241
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,480
Is it good?

242
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,320
Ziqi is here.

243
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:30,880
Mr. Gu.

244
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:31,760
Mr. Qin.

245
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:35,320
Eat slowly.

246
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,360
Perfect timing, Ziqi.

247
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:38,040
I have a meeting to attend in a while.

248
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,080
Come help me out.

249
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,360
Scrape this apple a bit finer.

250
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,160
Give this mashed apple to Mr. Qin.

251
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:43,720
Okay.

252
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:46,240
That won't happen.

253
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,240
Look at you nagging.

254
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:54,000
Rest well.

255
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,200
I'll come see you after I finish my work.

256
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,560
Bye, chatterbox.

257
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,400
Here, Mr. Qin.

258
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,560
Slow down.

259
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,720
How's the project progress?

260
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,000
It's going smoothly.

261
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:28,640
Can't you just tell me the truth?

262
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:33,160
According to the current timeline,

263
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:37,480
you shouldn't have time to run over here.

264
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:47,580
There's really no problem with the project.

265
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:51,080
Then there's a problem with the team.

266
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:59,880
I know you mean well.

267
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:01,440
You're afraid I'll worry.

268
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:04,520
But the more you hide it from me,

269
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:07,360
the more unsure I feel.

270
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:11,960
Here, Mr. Qin.

271
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:17,200
Don't worry.

272
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,840
There's really no major problem with the project.

273
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:20,760
Everything

274
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,490
is moving forward on schedule.

275
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:26,280
It's just that...

276
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,040
Xu Xu's standards might be too high.

277
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,720
Since entering physical car testing,

278
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,760
he's been constantly scrapping and restarting.

279
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:35,960
The software we're responsible for...

280
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:37,480
Keep revising.

281
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:43,970
Why are you here?

282
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:51,920
Come.

283
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:00,280
Come out for a second.

284
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:36,420
What did you say to Qin?

285
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:38,600
Nothing,

286
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:40,140
just reported on work.

287
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:44,280
He hasn't fully recovered yet.

288
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:45,880
Don't bother him with work

289
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:47,400
unless you have to.

290
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,160
You underestimate him too much.

291
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,280
Is it about underestimating him?

292
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:56,200
Anyway, I have the final say on Qin's matters now.

293
00:24:58,480 --> 00:24:59,560
Are you done?

294
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,080
What do you want?

295
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:02,080
All I did was not tell you

296
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:03,240
that he was sick.

297
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,320
There's nothing to talk about.

298
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:10,250
I have the final say regarding Qin.

299
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,760
Finish calculating your share of the data,

300
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:43,620
and then do Ying Ziqi's share too.

301
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:44,600
He quit.

302
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:48,320
He quit.

303
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:49,920
Quit?

304
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:51,120
Why?

305
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:53,280
He went to make his own proposal.

306
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:58,160
I'll do the proposal myself.

307
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:02,610
What exactly are you two doing?

308
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:04,080
I asked you to do the data.

309
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:06,200
Figure out what you're supposed to do.

310
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,520
Calculate the data first.

311
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,560
Did you hear me?

312
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,560
No need. Yours is flawed.

313
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:17,890
Are you going to do this task or not?

314
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:21,500
You'll see once it's done.

315
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:25,930
Where are you going?

316
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,130
Let me wipe your face before you sleep.

317
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,760
Just let me wipe it.

318
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,480
You see,

319
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:27,330
at the critical moment,

320
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,490
you still have to rely on me, right?

321
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:31,280
They say,

322
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:33,920
raise a son for your old age.

323
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,680
I heard about it.

324
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:36,960
They said

325
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:39,820
they wanted to introduce you to someone.

326
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,260
What about you?

327
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:43,640
You just flatly refused.

328
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:46,100
You should at least go take a look.

329
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:49,160
What if? What if you guys hit it off?

330
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,000
You regret it now, don't you?

331
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:52,600
Indeed.

332
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:54,480
You're worrying for nothing.

333
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:57,040
Let me wipe it for you.

334
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:57,600
So you can be comfortable.

335
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:59,120
No. Don't touch me.

336
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:00,400
Just a bit.

337
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,720
Don't touch.

338
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:02,760
You're all sweaty.

339
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:04,560
It's sticky and uncomfortable.

340
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:06,480
I don't want it.

341
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:07,320
Very quick.

342
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:08,680
Be good.

343
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:17,290
Isn't it much more comfortable to be fresh and clean?

344
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:30,440
I said I will take care of you for the rest of your life.

345
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:31,920
And I definitely will.

346
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:33,680
If you don't let me,

347
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:36,080
when you retire

348
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:37,600
and you're all alone,

349
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:39,120
by then,

350
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:41,200
when you want someone to wipe your face,

351
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,730
there will be no one to do it.

352
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:44,720
No.

353
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:45,920
It tickles.

354
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,520
Why is it ticklish?

355
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:48,640
Don't tense up.

356
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,880
If you tense up... No!

357
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,760
Come on. No!

358
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:54,040
I just have this problem of being ticklish.

359
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:55,520
It's not about tensing up.

360
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:56,240
No, the back of your neck.

361
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,240
Hurry, be good.

362
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,120
Okay.

363
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:58,960
Come on.

364
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,680
Slow down.

365
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:05,880
Done. Good.

366
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,930
Don't you feel much better?

367
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,160
I was going to give you a surprise.

368
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:21,280
But look at you, tensing up and not cooperating.

369
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,160
I guess forget it.

370
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,760
I'm cooperating. I did.

371
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:25,920
Did you?

372
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:27,680
I...

373
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,440
I cooperated.

374
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:31,280
What surprise?

375
00:29:40,160 --> 00:29:41,160
Look what this is.

376
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,760
Look whose baby this is.

377
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:49,080
How did you get this here?

378
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:51,920
You cherish this so much,

379
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,850
we definitely have to take good care of it for you.

380
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,920
Thank you for taking care of it for me.

381
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,240
Look.

382
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:04,160
Where are the buds?

383
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:05,000
What buds?

384
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:06,560
When I came out,

385
00:30:06,560 --> 00:30:08,360
there were buds on it.

386
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:11,900
It was like this when I brought it.

387
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,240
I had good intentions.

388
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,800
You can't falsely accuse me.

389
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:17,040
Who's falsely accusing you? Look,

390
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,320
the tips of the leaves are all yellow.

391
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:20,000
Here?

392
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,240
I actually looked it up.

393
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,240
They said

394
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:26,440
this is the natural metabolism of orchids.

395
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:29,480
Stop worrying about everything.

396
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,560
Worry about yourself.

397
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:33,320
I'm not worried about the orchids.

398
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:36,480
I'm worried about you guys.

399
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,560
Tell me the truth.

400
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,240
How is the mission going?

401
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:52,760
The mission is going well.

402
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,680
Everything is on track.

403
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:57,720
Then it must be you and Ying Ziqi.

404
00:30:57,720 --> 00:30:59,650
Are you two having problems again?

405
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:02,680
What problems could we have?

406
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:04,360
We're perfectly fine.

407
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:05,680
Let me tell you,

408
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,640
about my illness,

409
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,840
I told him not to tell you.

410
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,320
If you are angry,

411
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:14,120
take it out on me.

412
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,000
All right. Get some rest.

413
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:22,440
Sleep.

414
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:25,000
You're a big guy,

415
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,960
but why are you so petty?

416
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:29,760
How am I petty?

417
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:32,960
All right.

418
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:34,640
I'll lower the bed so you can sleep.

419
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:36,320
I'm not sleeping.

420
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:38,920
Go to sleep.

421
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:40,780
I've been busy all day.

422
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,560
If you're not sleeping, I am.

423
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,480
I'm not sleeping.

424
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:48,240
I'm not sleepy.

425
00:31:59,040 --> 00:31:59,520
Lao Xu.

426
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:01,880
I just finished work and saw your message.

427
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:03,810
You haven't contacted me for ages.

428
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:06,840
Are you under a lot of pressure from the task again?

429
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:08,680
Don't be too harsh on your subordinates.

430
00:32:08,680 --> 00:32:10,040
I believe you can do it.

431
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,680
Come on, Moon Rabbit 2.

432
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:14,120
Let bygones be bygones.

433
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:19,360
I saw your proposal.

434
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:21,520
After reading it,

435
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:22,760
I was quite inspired.

436
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:25,380
I did some finishing touches.

437
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:26,920
I think

438
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:28,600
we should integrate them

439
00:33:28,600 --> 00:33:29,660
and show it to Xu Xu.

440
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:33,500
Why are you taking it out on the punching bag?

441
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:35,090
Why are you so angry?

442
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:52,640
Punching bags are so boring.

443
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:54,610
You should fight a real person.

444
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:01,880
You want a real fight?

445
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:11,440
Fight. Aren't you going to fight?

446
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:12,400
Bring it.

447
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:13,800
Come hit me.

448
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:14,880
Are you that tough?

449
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:33,139
Are you a dog or something?

450
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:35,440
Just found out, huh?

451
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:36,800
I...

452
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:53,560
Do you yield?

453
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:54,760
Do you yield?

454
00:34:55,639 --> 00:34:56,960
I'm asking, do you yield?

455
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:58,280
Do you yield?

456
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:07,520
Do you yield?

457
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,200
Do you yield?

458
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:12,320
Do you yield?

459
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:13,480
Do you yield?

460
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,920
I'm asking, do you yield?

461
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:18,120
Do you yield?

462
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:21,480
Are you convinced?

463
00:35:31,440 --> 00:35:33,160
I wronged you about Qin.

464
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,930
But you shouldn't have kept it from me.

465
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:56,770
What about Xu Xu?

466
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:03,680
Since No.1 is his nightmare,

467
00:36:06,080 --> 00:36:08,240
let's work together

468
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:09,440
to make No.2 perfect.

469
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,760
You are my best brother.

470
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:24,520
Don't make me hit you a second time.

471
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,080
Say it again.

472
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:37,400
Don't let me...

473
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:39,200
Stop acting cool, bro.

474
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:50,440
You hit me so hard.

475
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:52,280
Can I get a new car?

476
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:54,760
I should get checked for a minor injury or something.

477
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:56,920
I went easy on you, I'll have you know.

478
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:58,760
If I hit you hard,

479
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,780
I would've knocked your head off.

480
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,520
You two pack your things and go back.

481
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,460
I already talked to Mr. Gu.

482
00:37:13,520 --> 00:37:15,450
With your attitude and abilities,

483
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:17,880
the infield is not suitable for you.

484
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:19,360
Whether we're suitable or not,

485
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,890
look at our proposal first.

486
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:22,080
I have no time.

487
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:25,400
We want to talk to you.

488
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:26,400
We think your mentality

489
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,660
and working style are very problematic.

490
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,360
Does it have anything to do with you?

491
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,080
We are on the same task.

492
00:37:35,240 --> 00:37:37,240
How can it have nothing to do with us?

493
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:39,280
You didn't trust us from the beginning,

494
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,010
didn't give us important work,

495
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:43,480
and carried all the pressure yourself.

496
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:44,850
Without teammates,

497
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:45,720
by yourself,

498
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:47,520
can you complete such a big task?

499
00:37:48,640 --> 00:37:49,970
I don't need teammates.

500
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,240
Even if I did,

501
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:54,170
it wouldn't be people like you.

502
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:55,800
I know you don't trust us,

503
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:58,660
but could you look at our proposal first?

504
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:04,000
Please.

505
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:16,520
One last time.

506
00:38:43,720 --> 00:38:44,480
Who did this?

507
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:46,160
We did it together.

508
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:47,400
A joint effort.

509
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:49,280
Teamwork.

510
00:38:55,560 --> 00:38:56,640
Look at you two.

511
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:59,380
Is this how you cooperate?

512
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,200
The model is fixed.

513
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:12,380
I still want you to have it.

514
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:44,120
We've completed our mission very well.

515
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,800
Don't treat a little regret

516
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,360
as a failure.

517
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:50,600
I know.

518
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:51,720
Stop talking, Lao Liu.

519
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:52,980
I don't want to hear it.

520
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:54,810
Let me sleep for a while.

521
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:58,920
I've applied for a transfer.

522
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:05,160
Wait.

523
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,240
I made the mistake.

524
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:10,680
Why are you transferring?

525
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,610
No, this has nothing to do with you.

526
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:15,720
I originally planned to leave

527
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:17,000
after this mission.

528
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:21,420
It's a bit sudden not discussing this with you beforehand.

529
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:24,200
Wait, Lao Liu.

530
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:28,680
But some decisions have to be made sooner or later.

531
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:32,760
Mr. Xu.

532
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:40,360
You are more talented

533
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:42,460
and more capable than I am.

534
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:45,000
You were born for this line of work.

535
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:46,880
Through this mission,

536
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:49,180
I've also realized my own limits.

537
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:52,240
I'm making a timely adjustment now.

538
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,520
I hope you can understand me.

539
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:00,210
I don't understand.

540
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:02,200
Alright.

541
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:04,760
I have to go.

542
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:08,210
I need to go report for duty.

543
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:24,160
For a very long time,

544
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:27,360
I couldn't let this go.

545
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:30,720
No matter how Mr. Liu tried to persuade me,

546
00:41:30,720 --> 00:41:32,520
I remained conflicted inside.

547
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:34,410
I couldn't forgive myself.

548
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:36,690
And Mr. Liu's departure

549
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:39,120
was even harder for me to accept,

550
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:42,200
hitting me harder than the setback at work.

551
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:52,960
114.8.

552
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:55,640
114.8 meters.

553
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:59,920
This is the rabbit's final travel distance.

554
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,980
I sent it to the moon with my own hands,

555
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,620
but failed to take good care of it.

556
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:07,760
Even now,

557
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:10,080
the image of it all alone on the moon

558
00:42:10,080 --> 00:42:12,680
still flashes before my eyes from time to time.

559
00:42:14,080 --> 00:42:15,360
It reminds me

560
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:17,040
that as an aerospace worker,

561
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:18,160
when carrying out a mission,

562
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:20,120
there is no room for a single mistake.

563
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:21,850
Even the slightest negligence

564
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:23,880
will cause everyone's hard work

565
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:25,010
to go down the drain.

566
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:38,610
Actually, it's not that I don't trust you.

567
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:40,880
I just want to do my best,

568
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,640
so I keep overturning things

569
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:43,700
and starting over,

570
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:46,800
constantly raising the requirements for you.

571
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:49,130
I don't want you to follow in my footsteps,

572
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:50,800
nor do I want

573
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:52,320
you to have

574
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:54,180
any regrets when doing a mission.

575
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,160
